<br>
<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">This filing relates solely to preliminary communications made before the commencement of a tender offer by KS Merger Sub Inc., a Delaware corporation (&#8220;Purchaser&#8221;) and a wholly-owned subsidiary of The Kroger Co., an Ohio corporation (&#8220;Kroger&#8221;), to purchase all of the shares of common stock, par value $0.01 per share, of Roundy&#8217;s, Inc., a Delaware corporation (&#8220;Roundy&#8217;s&#8221;), that are issued and outstanding at a price of $3.60 per share, net to the seller in cash, without interest, less any applicable withholding taxes, pursuant to an Agreement and Plan of Merger, dated as of November 10, 2015, by and among Purchaser, Kroger and Roundy&#8217;s.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Notice to Investors</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">The tender offer referenced in this press release has not yet commenced. This communication is for informational purposes only and is neither an offer to purchase nor a solicitation of an offer to sell shares of Roundy&#8217;s, Inc. (&#8220;Roundy&#8217;s&#8221;), nor is it a substitute for the tender offer materials that The Kroger Co. (&#8220;Parent&#8221;) and KS Merger Sub Inc. (&#8220;Acquisition Sub&#8221;), a wholly-owned subsidiary of Parent, will file with the Securities and Exchange Commission (&#8220;SEC&#8221;) upon commencement of the tender offer. At the time the tender offer is commenced, Parent and Acquisition Sub will file with the SEC tender offer materials on Schedule TO, and Roundy&#8217;s will file with the SEC a Solicitation/Recommendation Statement on Schedule 14D-9, with respect to the tender offer. The tender offer materials (including an Offer to Purchase, a related Letter of Transmittal and certain other tender offer documents) and the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement will contain important information. Holders of shares of Roundy&#8217;s are urged to read these documents carefully when they become available, because they will contain important information that holders of Roundy&#8217;s securities should consider before making any decision regarding tendering their securities. The Offer to Purchase, the related Letter of Transmittal and certain other tender offer documents, as well as the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement, will be made available to all holders of shares of Roundy&#8217;s at no expense to them. The tender offer materials and the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement will be made available for free at the SEC&#8217;s web site at www.sec.gov. Additional copies of the tender offer materials may be obtained at no charge by sending a written request to Parent at The Kroger Co., 1014 Vine Street, Cincinnati, OH 45202-1100, Attention: General Counsel.</font></div>

</tr><tr>
<td align="left" valign="top" width="8%">
<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">Exhibit 99.5</font></div>
</td>
<td valign="bottom" width="4%"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></td>
<td align="left" valign="top" width="78%">
<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">Questions &amp; Answers for Kroger Associates, distributed on November 11, 2015</font></div>
</td>
</tr><tr>

<DESCRIPTION>EX.99.1 - JOINT PRESS RELEASE

<div><font style="TEXT-DECORATION: underline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right"><font style="TEXT-DECORATION: underline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">EXHIBIT 99.1</font></div>

<div>&#160;</div>

<div>&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: left"><br>
</div>

<div>&#160;</div>

<div align="center">
<table bgcolor="white" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">
<tr>
<td width="42%" style="TEXT-ALIGN: right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><img src="mm11-1215_scto991img1.jpg" alt="kroger logo in 99.1">&#160;</font></td>
<td width="8%"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></td>
<td width="50%">
<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><img src="mm11-1215_scto991img2.jpg" alt="round's logo in 99.1">&#160;</font></div>
</td>
</tr></table>
</div>

<div><br>
<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 16pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger and Roundy&#8217;s Announce</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 16pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Definitive Merger Agreement</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div align="center"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 13pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger to Add Complementary Footprint of 151 Stores, Including</font></div>

<div align="center"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 13pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">New Wisconsin Geography and 34 Mariano&#8217;s Locations in Chicago</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">&#160;</div>

<div align="center"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 13pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Roundy&#8217;s Shareholders to Receive $3.60 Per Share in Cash;</font></div>

<div align="center"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 13pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Transaction Valued at Approximately $800 Million Including Debt</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline"><font style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">CINCINNATI, OH and MILWAUKEE, WI &#8211; November 11, 2015</font> &#8211; The Kroger Co. (NYSE: KR) and Roundy&#8217;s, Inc. (NYSE: RNDY) today announced a definitive merger agreement under which Kroger will purchase all outstanding shares of Roundy&#8217;s for $3.60 per share in cash.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">The transaction price represents a premium of approximately 65% to the Roundy&#8217;s closing share price on November 10, 2015. The terms of the agreement were unanimously approved by the Boards of Directors of both companies.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">Under the terms of the merger agreement, Kroger will commence a tender offer for all of the outstanding shares of Roundy&#8217;s common stock. Any shares of Roundy&#8217;s common stock not acquired in the tender offer will be acquired by Kroger in a subsequent merger. The transaction is subject to Roundy&#8217;s stockholders tendering at least a majority of the outstanding shares of Roundy&#8217;s common stock in the tender offer, certain regulatory approvals, and other customary closing conditions. The transaction is not subject to any financing conditions.&#160;&#160;Willis Stein &amp; Partners and its affiliates, holders of approximately 7% of the outstanding shares of Roundy&#8217;s common stock, have agreed to tender their shares. The transaction is expected to close before the end of the 2015 calendar year. The Merger Agreement contains a thirty (30) day go-shop period, which commences on the date of the Merger Agreement (the &#8220;Go-Shop Period&#8221;).</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#8220;We are delighted to welcome Roundy&#8217;s to the Kroger family,&#8221; said Rodney McMullen, Kroger's chairman and chief executive officer. &#8220;With a team of 22,000 talented associates, outstanding store locations, and a shared commitment to putting customers first, we are excited about Roundy&#8217;s future growth.&#8221;</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#8220;Mergers for Kroger always involve both parties bringing something to the table,&#8221; Mr. McMullen said. &#8220;We admire what Bob Mariano has done with the Mariano&#8217;s banner in Chicago, where he has created an urban format that is resonating with customers and we expect to apply Roundy&#8217;s experience<font style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font>to our stores in urban areas around the country. Kroger&#8217;s scale and strong financial position will enable Roundy&#8217;s to reinvest in its home state of Wisconsin while continuing to grow in Chicago. Together, we are committed to investing in Roundy&#8217;s people, communities, stores and merchandising to deliver a fantastic customer experience that will create opportunities for associates, grow customer loyalty and revenue, and create value for shareholders.&#8221;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font size="3">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font size="3">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font size="3">&#160;</font></div>

<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>
</div>

<div id="PN" style="WIDTH: 100%; PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; DISPLAY: inline">1</font></div>

<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
<hr style="COLOR: indianred" noshade size="2">
</div>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>
</div>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font size="3">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left">
<div><font size="3">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<table bgcolor="white" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">
<tr>
<td width="42%" style="TEXT-ALIGN: right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><img src="mm11-1215_scto991img1.jpg" alt="kroger logo in 99.1">&#160;</font></td>
<td width="8%"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></td>
<td width="50%">
<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><img src="mm11-1215_scto991img2.jpg" alt="round's logo in 99.1">&#160;</font></div>
</td>
</tr></table>
</div>

<div><font size="3"><br>
</font></div>
</div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">Robert A. Mariano, chairman of the board, president and chief executive officer of Roundy&#8217;s, Inc. said, &#8220;We are excited about becoming part of The Kroger Co. Kroger&#8217;s scale, knowledge and experience allows us to accelerate the strategic initiatives we have invested in and makes us a more formidable competitor in the marketplace. This is a great win for our customers, communities,&#160;&#160;employees and our shareholders, and I personally look forward to continue to exceed customer and employee expectations. &#8221;</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">Roundy&#8217;s brings to Kroger an expanded footprint with a complementary base of 151 stores and 101 pharmacies in new geographies including Milwaukee, Madison and Northern Wisconsin, which are served under the Pick &#8216;n Save, Copps and Metro Market banners. The merger also expands Kroger&#8217;s presence with an innovative store format in the Chicagoland area, where Roundy&#8217;s operates 34 stores under the Mariano&#8217;s banner. Roundy&#8217;s also operates two distribution centers in Oconomowoc and Mazomanie, WI, and a commissary in Kenosha, WI. Roundy&#8217;s had revenues of nearly $4.0 billion for fiscal year 2014.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Financial Highlights</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger plans to finance the transaction with debt, and refinance Roundy&#8217;s existing debt of $646 million based on market conditions. Consistent with the company&#8217;s long-term commitment to returning cash to shareholders, Kroger intends to continue its quarterly dividend and share repurchase program while managing free cash flow to reduce the leverage taken on from this merger. Although the company&#8217;s net debt to EBITDA ratio will increase at the time the merger closes, Kroger expects the ratio to remain in the 2.00 &#8211; 2.20 range upon closing of the merger. Kroger is committed to maintaining its current investment grade credit rating.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger expects the merger to be slightly accretive to earnings in the first full year after closing, excluding merger-related expenses. The transaction will have no effect on Kroger&#8217;s current long-term net earnings per diluted share growth rate of 8 &#8211; 11%, plus a growing dividend.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">While Kroger expects to realize cost savings of approximately $40 million over time, the company plans to reinvest those cost savings to grow the business. Kroger has a strong history of achieving synergy goals. Being patient in achieving those goals reduces the risk of the transaction and sets the stage for sustainable growth.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operational Profile</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">Together Kroger and Roundy&#8217;s will operate 2,774 supermarkets and employ over 422,000 associates across 35 states and the District of Columbia. Following closing, Roundy&#8217;s will continue to operate its stores as a subsidiary of The Kroger Co. and will continue to be led by key members of Roundy&#8217;s senior management team. There are no plans to close stores, and associates will have employment opportunities with both companies. Roundy&#8217;s headquarters will remain in Milwaukee, WI.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger and Roundy&#8217;s both strive to play a vital role in all of the communities they serve. In 2014, Kroger invested more than $280 million in local communities to provide hunger relief and support for the military and their families, breast cancer awareness programs and more than 30,000 schools </font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>
</div>

<div id="PN" style="WIDTH: 100%; PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; DISPLAY: inline">2</font></div>

<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
<hr style="COLOR: indianred" noshade size="2">
</div>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>
</div>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left">
<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<table bgcolor="white" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; TEXT-INDENT: 9pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">
<tr style="TEXT-INDENT: 9pt;">
<td width="42%" style="TEXT-ALIGN: right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><img src="mm11-1215_scto991img1.jpg" alt="kroger logo in 99.1">&#160;</font></td>
<td width="8%"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></td>
<td width="50%">
<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><img src="mm11-1215_scto991img2.jpg" alt="round's logo in 99.1">&#160;</font></div>
</td>
</tr></table>
</div>

<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline"><br>
</font></div>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">and grassroots organizations.&#160;&#160;Roundy&#8217;s is similarly committed to helping communities through the Roundy&#8217;s Foundation. Chartered in 2003, the Roundy&#8217;s Foundation mission is to support organizations working to relieve hunger and helping families in crisis due to domestic abuse, neglect and other at-risk situations.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Additional Information</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">The transaction is expected to close by the end of the 2015 calendar year following the satisfaction of customary closing conditions, including successful completion of the tender offer and regulatory approval. The transaction includes customary breakup fees.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">BofA Merrill Lynch and Sagent Advisors, LLC are acting as financial advisors to Kroger and Weil, Gotshal &amp; Manges LLP is acting as legal advisor to Kroger.&#160;&#160;J.P. Morgan Securities LLC is acting as exclusive financial advisor to Roundy&#8217;s and provided a fairness opinion to its Board of Directors. Kirkland &amp; Ellis LLP is acting as legal advisor to Roundy&#8217;s.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Conference Call Today</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger chief financial officer Mike Schlotman will host a conference call for analysts and investors today, November 11, 2015, at 11:00 a.m. (ET) to discuss this announcement in further detail. To join this conference call, visit ir.kroger.com. An on-demand replay of the webcast will be available from approximately 1:00 p.m. (ET) today through Wednesday, November 25, 2015.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">About Kroger</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger, one of the world's largest retailers, employs nearly 400,000 associates who serve customers in 2,623 supermarkets and multi-department stores in 34 states and the District of Columbia under two dozen local banner names including Kroger, City Market, Dillons, Food 4 Less, Fred Meyer, Fry's, Harris Teeter, Jay C, King Soopers, QFC, Ralphs and Smith's.&#160;&#160;The company also operates 781 convenience stores, 327 fine jewelry stores, 1,350 supermarket fuel centers and 37 food processing plants in the U.S.&#160;&#160;Recognized by Forbes as the most generous company in America, Kroger supports hunger relief, breast cancer awareness, the military and their families, and more than 30,000 schools and community organizations. Kroger contributes food and funds equal to 200 million meals a year through more than 100 Feeding America food bank partners. A leader in supplier diversity, Kroger is a proud member of the Billion Dollar Roundtable and the U.S. Hispanic Chamber's Million Dollar Club.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">About Roundy&#8217;s, Inc.</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">Roundy&#8217;s is a leading grocer in the Midwest with nearly $4.0 billion in sales and more than 22,000 employees. Founded in Milwaukee in 1872, Roundy&#8217;s operates 151 retail grocery stores and 101 pharmacies under the Copps, Pick &#8217;n Save, Metro Market and Mariano&#8217;s retail banners in Wisconsin and Illinois. Roundy&#8217;s is committed to helping the communities its stores serve through the Roundy&#8217;s Foundation. Chartered in 2003, the Roundy&#8217;s Foundation mission is to support organizations working to relieve hunger and helping families in crisis due to domestic abuse, neglect and other at-risk situations.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left">

</font><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Additional Information and Where to Find It</font></div>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">The tender offer referenced in this press release has not yet commenced. This communication is for informational purposes only and is neither an offer to purchase nor a solicitation of an offer to sell shares of Roundy&#8217;s, Inc. (&#8220;Roundy&#8217;s&#8221;), nor is it a substitute for the tender offer materials that The Kroger Co. (&#8220;Parent&#8221;) and KS Merger Sub Inc. (&#8220;Acquisition Sub&#8221;), a wholly-owned subsidiary of Parent, will file with the Securities and Exchange Commission (&#8220;SEC&#8221;) upon commencement of the tender offer. At the time the tender offer is commenced, Parent and Acquisition Sub will file with the SEC tender offer materials on Schedule TO, and Roundy&#8217;s will file with the SEC a Solicitation/Recommendation Statement on Schedule 14D-9, with respect to the tender offer. The tender offer materials (including an Offer to Purchase, a related Letter of Transmittal and certain other tender offer documents) and the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement will contain important information. Holders of shares of Roundy&#8217;s are urged to read these documents carefully when they become available, because they will contain important information that holders of Roundy&#8217;s securities should consider before making any decision regarding tendering their securities. The Offer to Purchase, the related Letter of Transmittal and certain other tender offer documents, as well as the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement, will be made available to all holders of shares of Roundy&#8217;s at no expense to them. The tender offer materials and the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement will be made available for free at the SEC&#8217;s web site at www.sec.gov. Additional copies of the tender offer materials may be obtained at no charge by sending a written request to Parent at The Kroger Co., 1014 Vine Street, Cincinnati, OH 45202-1100, Attention: General Counsel.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Forward-Looking Statements</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: -13.7pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">This press release contains certain forward-looking statements about the future performance of Kroger. These statements are based on management's assumptions and beliefs in light of the information currently available to it. These statements are indicated by words such as "expect," "intend," "guidance,&#8221; &#8220;will" and similar words.&#160;&#160;Various uncertainties and other factors could cause actual results to differ materially from those contained in the forward-looking statements. These include the specific risk factors identified in "Risk Factors" and "Outlook" in Kroger&#8217;s annual report on Form 10-K for our last fiscal year and any subsequent filings, as well as the following:</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<DESCRIPTION>EX.99.2 - DISCUSSION GUIDE FROM MIKE SCHLOTMAN
<TEXT>
<html>
<head>
    <title>mm11-1215_scto993.htm</title>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">
<div>&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; TEXT-DECORATION: underline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">EXHIBIT 99.2</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right">&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: left"><img src="mm11-1215_scto993p1.jpg" alt=""></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: left">&#160;</div>

<div align="center">
<table bgcolor="white" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">
<tr>
<td width="50%"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" size="6" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial">Kroger &amp; Roundy&#8217;s Announce Merger Agreement</font></font> </font>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial; DISPLAY: inline">The Kroger Co. and Roundy&#8217;s, Inc., today announced an agreement to form a merger of the two companies. This strategic partnership will give both retailers &#8211; and associates at each company &#8211; more opportunities to grow and serve our customers in key areas.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial; DISPLAY: inline">NOVEMBER 11, 2015</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">The Highlights:</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#61623; As part of the agreement, Kroger will purchase all outstanding shares of Roundy&#8217;s for $3.60 per share in cash. The transaction is valued at approximately $800 million, including debt.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#61623; The terms of the agreement were unanimously approved by the Boards of Directors of both companies. Kroger will commence a tender offer for all of the outstanding shares of Roundy&#8217;s common stock.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#61623; Based in Milwaukee, Roundy&#8217;s has more than 22,000 associates who work in and support 151 supermarkets and 101 pharmacies in Wisconsin, including Milwaukee, Madison and Northern Wisconsin. These associates work in Pick &#8216;n Save, Copps and Metro Market banner stores. Roundy&#8217;s associates in the Chicago area serve customers at 34 Mariano&#8217;s supermarkets.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#61623; The company also operates two distribution centers in Oconomowoc and Mazomanie, Wis., and a commissary in Kenosha, Wis.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#61623; This merger fits our strategy to fill in some existing geographic areas and enter attractive new ones where we can use existing infrastructure and logistics networks.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#61623; Roundy&#8217;s will operate as a subsidiary of Kroger from its current headquarters. We will rely on key members of their senior management</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial; DISPLAY: inline">team to continue to run Roundy&#8217;s, including their current president and CEO Bob Mariano, who will serve as president of this new division.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#61623; Together, we will have more than 422,000 associates who serve customers in 2,774 stores in 35 states and the District of Columbia.</font></font></div>
</td>
<td width="50%"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160; </font>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">&#8220;</font>We are so excited to welcome Roundy&#8217;s to the Kroger family.</font></font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">With a team of more than 22,000 talented associates, outstanding store locations and a shared commitment to putting customers first, Roundy&#8217;s has a lot of opportunity for growth.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">Together, we are committed to investing in Roundy&#8217;s people, communities, stores and merchandising to deliver a fantastic customer experience that will create opportunities for associates, grow customer loyalty and revenue, and create value for shareholders.&#8221;</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">&#8213;</font><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Rodney McMullen, Kroger Chairman &amp; CEO</font></font></font></font></div>
</td>
</tr></table>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>

<div><img src="mm11-1215_scto993p2a.jpg" alt=""></div>

<div align="center">
<table bgcolor="white" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">
<tr>
<td width="50%">

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">&#8220;We are confident that with our scale, loyalty programs and strong balance sheet, combined with the capable, knowledgeable Roundy&#8217;s associates and superior store locations, we can grow the Wisconsin markets. At the same time, we are excited to learn about and leverage key findings from Mariano&#8217;s experiences in Chicago.&#8221;</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">&#8211; </font><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman, Kroger Executive Vice President &amp; CFO</font></font></font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">More About Roundy&#8217;s:</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">Like Kroger, Roundy&#8217;s has a long and rich history. The company was founded in 1872, when Judson A. Roundy and two partners, Sidney Hauxhurst and William A. Smith, founded a wholesale grocery company called Smith, Roundy &amp; Co. in Milwaukee. From there, the company began to grow.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Key Milestones:</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">1902: </font>The firm incorporates as Roundy&#8217;s, Peckham &amp; Dexter Co.</font></font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">1922: </font>Roundy&#8217;s begins to offer its own brand of products.</font></font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">1975: </font>The company opens a Pick &#8216;n Save Warehouse Foods store.</font></font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">2001: </font>Roundy&#8217;s purchases Copps Food Centers, the largest family-owned supermarket chain in Wisconsin at the time.</font></font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">2010: </font>The company launches Mariano&#8217;s in the Chicago metropolitan area, offering world-class shopping and customer service.</font></font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">2012: </font>Roundy&#8217;s goes public on February 8, trading on the New York Stock Exchange as RNDY.</font></font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Other Facts:</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">&#61623; The company operates 34 Mariano&#8217;s stores in Chicago and 117 supermarkets in Wisconsin under three banners: 88 Pick &#8216;n Save stores, mainly in the Milwaukee area, 25 Copps stores and four Metro Market stores.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">&#61623; Roundy&#8217;s has approximately $4 billion in total annual sales.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">&#61623; The company has a strong commitment to health and wellness, sustainability and giving back to their communities.</font></font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">What&#8217;s next?</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">Stores in Kroger&#8217;s family of companies and Roundy&#8217;s will continue to operate as usual while we wait for completion of the tender offer and customary approvals. The merger is expected to close by the end of the calendar year. After closing, we will keep leaders and associates informed of our key integration steps and progress on an ongoing basis.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">Our goal in this process is to support the continued success of Roundy&#8217;s and Kroger as we combine our companies. We believe that this merger will strengthen both of our organizations and deepen our connections with our customers and communities.</font></font></font></div>
</td>
<td width="50%">

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">&#8220;We are excited about becoming part of The Kroger Co. Kroger&#8217;s scale, knowledge and experience allows us to accelerate the strategic initiatives we have invested in and makes us a more formidable competitor in the marketplace. This a great win for our customers, communities, employees and our shareholders, and I personally look forward to continue to exceed customer and employee expectations.&#8221;</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 2pt; FONT-FAMILY: calibri; DISPLAY: inline">&#8210; </font>Bob Mariano, Chairman, President &amp; CEO, Roundy&#8217;s, Inc</font></font></font></div>
</td>
</tr></table>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Additional Information and Where to Find It </font>The tender offer referenced herein has not yet commenced. This communication is for informational purposes only and is neither an offer to purchase nor a solicitation of an offer to sell shares of Roundy&#8217;s, Inc. (&#8220;Roundy&#8217;s&#8221;), nor is it a substitute for the tender offer materials that The Kroger Co. (&#8220;Parent&#8221;) and KS Merger Sub Inc. (&#8220;Acquisition Sub&#8221;), a wholly-owned subsidiary of Parent, will file with the Securities and Exchange Commission (&#8220;SEC&#8221;) upon commencement of the tender offer. At the time the tender offer is commenced, Parent and Acquisition Sub will file with the SEC tender offer materials on Schedule TO, and Roundy&#8217;s will file with the SEC a Solicitation/Recommendation Statement on Schedule 14D-9, with respect to the tender offer. The tender offer materials (including an Offer to Purchase, a related Letter of Transmittal and certain other tender offer documents) and the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement will contain important information. Holders of shares of Roundy&#8217;s are urged to read these documents carefully when they become available, because they will contain important information that holders of Roundy&#8217;s securities should consider before making any decision regarding tendering their securities. The Offer to Purchase, the related Letter of Transmittal and certain other tender offer documents, as well as the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement, will be made available to all holders of shares of Roundy&#8217;s at no expense to them. The tender offer materials and the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement will be made available for free at the SEC&#8217;s web site at www.sec.gov. Additional copies of the tender offer materials may be obtained at no charge by sending a written request to Parent at The Kroger Co., 1014 Vine Street, Cincinnati, OH 45202-1100, Attention: General Counsel.</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Forward-Looking Statements</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">This document contains certain forward-looking statements about the future performance of Kroger. These statements are based on management's assumptions and beliefs in light of the information currently available to it. These statements are indicated by words such as "expect," "intend," "guidance,&#8221; &#8220;will" and similar words. Various uncertainties and other factors could cause actual results to differ materially from those contained in the forward-looking statements. These include the specific risk factors identified in "Risk Factors" and "Outlook" in Kroger&#8217;s annual report on Form 10-K for our last fiscal year and any subsequent filings, as well as the following:</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri">&#61623; <font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger&#8217;s ability to achieve sales, earnings and cash flow goals may be affected by: labor negotiations or disputes; changes in the types and numbers of businesses that compete with Kroger; pricing and promotional activities of existing and new competitors, including non-traditional competitors, and the aggressiveness of that competition; Kroger&#8217;s response to these actions; the state of the economy, including interest rates, the inflationary and deflationary trends in certain commodities, and the unemployment rate; the effect that fuel costs have on consumer spending; volatility of fuel margins; changes in government-funded benefit programs; manufacturing commodity costs; diesel fuel costs related to Kroger&#8217;s logistics operations; trends in consumer spending; the extent to which Kroger&#8217;s customers exercise caution in their purchasing in response to economic conditions; the inconsistent pace of the economic recovery; changes in inflation or deflation in product and operating costs; stock repurchases; Kroger&#8217;s ability to retain pharmacy sales from third party payors; consolidation in the healthcare industry, including pharmacy benefit managers; Kroger&#8217;s ability to negotiate modifications to multi-</font></font></font></div>

<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>

<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>

<div><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">employer pension plans; natural disasters or adverse weather conditions; the potential costs and risks associated with potential cyber-attacks or data security breaches; the success of Kroger&#8217;s future growth plans; and the successful integration of Harris Teeter and Roundy&#8217;s. Kroger&#8217;s ability to achieve sales and earnings goals may also be affected by Kroger&#8217;s ability to manage the factors identified above.</font></div>

<div>
<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri">&#61623; <font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger&#8217;s ability to use cash flow to continue to repurchase shares, fund dividends, increase capital investments, and maintain Kroger&#8217;s investment grade debt rating could be affected by unanticipated increases in net total debt, Kroger&#8217;s inability to generate cash flow at the levels anticipated, and Kroger&#8217;s failure to generate expected earnings.</font></font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri">&#61623; <font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger&#8217;s commencement of a tender offer will be contingent upon the merger agreement not being terminated prior to the commencement of the offer. The requirement to consummate the merger will be contingent upon the merger agreement being in effect and the conditions to the merger being satisfied or waived. The closing of the transaction could fail to occur before the end of calendar year 2015 if the tender offer does not achieve the anticipated results, if the conditions to closing are not satisfied or are not satisfied in a timely manner, or if the merger agreement is terminated as provided in the agreement.</font></font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; DISPLAY: inline"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri">&#61623; <font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger&#8217;s ability to finance the transaction with debt will depend on the availability of the debt markets, including commercial paper, our credit facility, and other sources of debt financing.</font></font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font color="transparent" style="FONT-SIZE: 1pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger assumes no obligation to update the information contained herein. Please refer to Kroger's reports and filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission for a further discussion of these risks and uncertainties.</font></div>
</div>
</body>

<DESCRIPTION>EX.99.3 - NEWSLETTER FROM MIKE SCHLOTMAN
<TEXT>
<html>

    <title>mm11-1215_scto992.htm</title>
