<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right"><br>
<font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">1</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">PRESENTATION</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operator</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Good morning, and welcome to the Kroger Company Investor Conference call.&#160;&#160;All participants will be in listen-only mode.&#160;&#160;Should you need assistance, please signal a conference specialist by pressing the star key followed by zero.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">After today&#8217;s presentation there will be an opportunity to ask questions.&#160;&#160;To ask a question, you may press star then one on your telephone keypad.&#160;&#160;To withdraw your question, please press star then two.&#160;&#160;Please note this event is being recorded.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I would now like to turn the conference over to Cindy Holmes, Director of Investor Relations.&#160;&#160;Please go ahead.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Cindy Holmes</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Thank you, Laura.&#160;&#160;Good morning, and thank you for joining us on short notice today.&#160;&#160;Before we begin, I want to remind you that today&#8217;s discussion will include forward-looking statements.&#160;&#160;We want to caution you that such statements are predictions, and actual events or results can differ materially.&#160;&#160;And none of these statements constitutes an offer to sell any securities.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">A detailed discussion of the many factors that we believe may have a material effect on our business on an ongoing basis is contained in our SEC filings.&#160;&#160;But, Kroger assumes no obligation to update that information.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Both our press release and our prepared remarks from this conference call will be available on our website at ir.kroger.com.&#160;&#160;After our prepared remarks, we look forward to taking your questions.&#160;&#160;We ask that you please limit yourself to one question and one follow-up question if necessary.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I&#8217;ll now turn the call over to Mike Schlotman, Kroger&#8217;s Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer.&#160;&#160;Mike.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Thanks, Cindy, and good morning, everyone.&#160;&#160;Before I begin with our prepared comments, I wanted to thank all the veterans on today, which is Veteran&#8217;s Day, for their service to the country.&#160;&#160;We know we&#8217;ve hired more than 32,000 veterans since 2009.&#160;&#160;And in fact, on September 15<font style="FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top; DISPLAY: inline">th</font>, we had a hiring day for veterans and on that day alone, hired over 2,000 veterans and their family members.&#160;&#160;So, we&#8217;re proud to have these folks working for us, and we&#8217;re proud for all they&#8217;ve done to serve our country.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">As we announced this morning, Roundy&#8217;s Inc. and Kroger will be merging in a transaction valued at approximately $800 million.&#160;&#160;We are excited to welcome Roundy&#8217;s to the Kroger family of companies.&#160;&#160;Like Kroger, Roundy&#8217;s talented team of associates is committed to putting the customer first.&#160;&#160;And by combining our financial strength with Roundy&#8217;s outstanding people and store locations, we see significant potential for growth in both the Roundy&#8217;s home state of Wisconsin and in the Chicago area.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">As Rodney in our press release this morning, we have great admiration for what Bob Mariano has accomplished with the Mariano&#8217;s banners in Chicago, effectively entering a new market organically, and creating a successful urban format that customers love.&#160;&#160;We expect to learn from these accomplishments to further Kroger&#8217;s penetration into urban markets.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Roundy&#8217;s expands Kroger&#8217;s footprint to several new contiguous markets, such as Milwaukee, Madison, </font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify">
<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div>
<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; DISPLAY: inline">The Kroger Company</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; DISPLAY: inline">November 11, 2015 at 11:00 a.m. Eastern</font></font></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>
</div>

<div id="PN" style="WIDTH: 100%; PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>

<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
<hr style="COLOR: indianred" noshade size="2">
</div>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>
</div>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><font size="2" style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">2</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">&#160;</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">and Northern Wisconsin, which are severed under Pick &#8216;n Save, Cobbs, and the Metro Market banners.&#160;&#160;The transaction also establishes a greater presence for Kroger in the Chicago area with 34 Mariano&#8217;s locations.&#160;&#160;Roundy&#8217;s has a total store count of 151 stores, including 101 pharmacies, 2 existing distribution centers, and one commissary to provide infrastructure support.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger has a long history of successfully integrating with merger partners, sharing the best of what each company has to offer while maintaining and enhancing district traits or brands that has made each great.&#160;&#160;This is evidenced not only by our major mergers with Dillions in 1983 and Fred Meyer 1999, but more recently with Harris Teeter in 2014.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">This merger is consistent with our growth strategy to enter new markets and fill in existing markets, and is similar to our previous transactions in a number of ways.&#160;&#160;Roundy&#8217;s has a solid market share in Wisconsin, and we plan to invest to grow the business.&#160;&#160;Mariano&#8217;s is among the best stores in the United States with a strong customer connection.&#160;&#160;And as with previous mergers, both parties bring something to the transaction.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Mariano&#8217;s has the unique urban format, and a great connection with customers.&#160;&#160;We expect to share best practices across all the banners, and make improvements where it makes sense.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger brings cost leverage and scale in systems, procurement, and manufacturing, plus our loyalty card, Insights, to benefit customers.&#160;&#160;We are confident that combining Kroger&#8217;s advantages with Roundy&#8217;s capable and knowledgeable associates and superior store locations we can grow the business over time.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Now, I&#8217;ll discuss Roundy&#8217;s operations in more detail, and how we think about their markets and customers.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">As I mentioned previously, Roundy&#8217;s operates a total of 151 stories, 101 of which have pharmacies.&#160;&#160;Looking more closely to their footprint, there are 88 Pick &#8216;n Save stores, primarily in Milwaukee, but also in Racine, Oshkosh, Kenosha, and Fond du Lac; 15 Cobb stores in Madison, Central and Northern Wisconsin; 4 Metro Market stores, one each in downtown Milwaukee, Brookfield, Madison, and Mequon, and 34 Mariano&#8217;s stores in Chicagoland.&#160;&#160;The Mariano&#8217;s locations will complement the 13 no frills warehouse format stores Kroger operates in Chicago under the Food 4 Less banner.&#160;&#160;We expect to be able to secure regulatory approval quickly.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Roundy&#8217;s operates two distribution center and one commissary in Wisconsin.&#160;&#160;The company employs over 22,000 associates, and had revenues of nearly $4 billion for the fiscal year ended January 3, 2015.&#160;&#160;As you know, we take integration very seriously, and we&#8217;ll work diligently together to develop plans to capture all the benefits of a transaction for Kroger, Roundy&#8217;s, our shareholders, associates, customers, and the communities we serve.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Following closing, Roundy&#8217;s will continue to operate stores as a subsidiary of the Kroger Co, and continue to be led by key members of Roundy&#8217;s senior management team.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I realize that many of Roundy&#8217;s associates will be curious about the plans for their stores and markets.&#160;&#160;While there are operational questions that will be answered in the coming months, we see Roundy&#8217;s as a strong merchant and expect to grow their franchises just as we expect to grow the Kroger franchise.&#160;&#160;We have no plans to close stores, and associates will have employment opportunities with both companies.&#160;&#160;We will examine everything in the context of the company&#8217;s growth, and we&#8217;ll be in a position to share more about our plans when the transaction closes.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify">
<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div>
<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; DISPLAY: inline">The Kroger Company</font></font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; DISPLAY: inline">November 11, 2015 at 11:00 a.m. Eastern</font></font></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>

<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>

<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
<hr style="COLOR: indianred" noshade size="2">
</div>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; DISPLAY: inline">&#160; </font></div>
</div>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><font size="2" style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">3</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Finally, I will outline the financial elements of the proposed merger.&#160;&#160;&#160;Under the terms of the merger agreement, which has been unanimously approved by both boards of directors, Kroger will purchase all outstanding shares of Roundy&#8217;s for $3.60 per share in cash. The transaction represents a premium of approximately 65% to Roundy&#8217;s closing price yesterday.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger will commence a tender offer for all the outstanding shares of Roundy&#8217;s common stock.&#160;&#160;The transaction is subject to Roundy&#8217;s shareholders tendering at a least a majority of the shares of Roundy&#8217;s common stock in the tender offer, certain regulatory approvals and other customary closing conditions.&#160;&#160;Willis Stein &amp; Partners and its affiliates, holders of approximately 7% of the outstanding shares of Roundy&#8217;s common stock, have agreed to tender their shares.&#160;&#160;We expect to close this transaction by the end of the 2015 calendar year.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger will finance the transaction with debt, and plans to refinance Roundy&#8217;s existing debt based on market conditions.&#160;&#160;Consistent with Kroger&#8217;s long-term commitment of returning cash to shareholders, Kroger intends to continue its quarterly dividend and share repurchase program while managing free cash flow to reduce the leverage taken on in connection with this merger.&#160;&#160;Although the company&#8217;s debt-to-EBITDA ratio will increase at the time the merger closes, Kroger expects the ratio to remain within the two to 2.5 times, which is where we target it.&#160;&#160;We are committed to maintaining our current investment grade rating.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger expects the deal to be slightly accretive in the first full year after closing, excluding merger-related expenses.&#160;&#160;The transaction will have no effect on Kroger&#8217;s current long-term net earnings per diluted share growth rate of 8% to 11% plus a growing dividend.&#160;&#160;Kroger expects to achieve synergies of approximately $40 million over time, and anticipates that most of these savings will be reinvested to the benefit of Roundy&#8217;s customers and to grow revenues, which will then benefit our shareholders.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Kroger has a strong history of achieving synergy goals.&#160;&#160;Being patient in achieving those goals reduces the risk of the transaction, and sets the stage for sustainable growth.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">In summary, the combined organization will operate 2,774 supermarkets, and employ over 422,000 associates across 35 states and the District of Columbia.&#160;&#160;The Kroger team is excited about this opportunity to work together with Roundy&#8217;s to invest in Roundy&#8217;s people and communities, to grow customer loyalty and revenues over the next several years.&#160;&#160;I&#8217;m now happy to take your questions.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operator</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">At this time, we will begin the question and answer session.&#160;&#160;To ask a question, you may press star then one on your telephone keypad.&#160;&#160;If you are using a speakerphone, please pick up your handset before pressing the keys.&#160;&#160;To withdraw your question, please press star then two.&#160;&#160;At this time, we will pause momentarily to assemble our roster.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And our first question will come from John Heinbockel of Guggenheim Securities.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">John Heinbockel</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, Mike, two things.&#160;&#160;First, just strategically, do you guys envision Bob&#8217;s role just running Roundy&#8217;s directly, or something more significant longer-term?&#160;&#160;I know he&#8217;s 65, but I think about his merchandising skills and that certainly can help the entire company.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And then, what do you think, particularly maybe on the fresh side, you pick up here that you didn&#8217;t have with Harris Teeter?&#160;&#160;Is it simply urban versus more suburban?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">&#160;</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Well, first on Bob, he is very energized and excited by this transaction, and he is excited to become part of our team.&#160;&#160;I wouldn&#8217;t venture to guess what his future role will be.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;re clearly going to need him to help drive the results we expect to get both in Chicago and as we make investments in Wisconsin, be part of bringing that team together to driving better sale results, as well as a better experience for not only our customers, but our associates as well.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">From a fresh standpoint, John, I think when you go to the stores in Chicago, there are a lot of interesting things that Bob and his team have done in Chicago.&#160;&#160;Fred and his team have done a lot of interesting things with their urban formats and Harris Teeter.&#160;&#160;And just like we&#8217;ve picked up things from Harris Teeter, I think there&#8217;ll be incremental ideas and processes we can pick up from Bob and what he&#8217;s done in Chicago.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Some of the unique things they do; for instance, some of their coffee shops, they have a local roaster come in to the stores and run the coffee shop.&#160;&#160;That&#8217;s the same guy that people see down the street.&#160;&#160;So, they have a big focus on finding that local feel inside the store so that it&#8217;s more than just a grocery store.&#160;&#160;It&#8217;s an experience of other opportunities that are in and around the neighborhoods.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We&#8217;ve done that a little bit in a few Kroger stores.&#160;&#160;There&#8217;s a couple in our Indianapolis division.&#160;&#160;There&#8217;s one in Lexington where we have almost a food truck kind of feel inside the store where these local merchants have a section of the store where they have their product available for purchase by our customers.&#160;&#160;And this, I think, we had the opportunity to take that to another level.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">John Heinbockel</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">All right.&#160;&#160;Then secondly, more tactically, obviously their EBITDA was down in the last quarter.&#160;&#160;The environment is difficult competitively.&#160;&#160;But, do you think, and you made the comment of reinvesting the synergies.&#160;&#160;Are the margins too high today in that market for that in particularly?&#160;&#160;So, that needs to be reset perhaps.&#160;&#160;And then going forward, I guess you would expect most of the EBITDA growth, even with that kind of market share, to come from top line, and I guess in Wisconsin, a lot of it would come from additional incremental share.&#160;&#160;Is that fair?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">John, when we look at where Roundy&#8217;s is, it feels very similar to a journey we&#8217;ve been on for the last 10 or 12 years with our Customer First journey.&#160;&#160;They aren&#8217;t starting at the beginning of where we started our Customer First journey.&#160;&#160;They&#8217;ve made some investments in price.&#160;&#160;I would say from a competitive pricing standpoint, they&#8217;re in better position today than when we started our Customer First journey.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, there will be some investment in all four keys of the Customer First - people, product, shopping experience, and price.&#160;&#160;We clearly see a path where we can grow revenue, particularly in Wisconsin with the number of stores they have.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;re thrilled with the real estate sites.&#160;&#160;They&#8217;re well situated.&#160;&#160;Over 80% of these sites we would rate A or B+.&#160;&#160;So, it&#8217;s great real estate.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We may need to invest some in infrastructure, may need to invest some in some more hours in some of the service departments, but those are things we know how to do and can do.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;re just really thrilled with this opportunity, joining with Bob.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And you look at markets like Milwaukee and Madison.&#160;&#160;They feel like other markets that Kroger operates in today in the Midwest, whether it&#8217;s Indianapolis, or Columbus, or Louisville.&#160;&#160;It just feels like home almost when you&#8217;re there making the stores.&#160;&#160;Just the values of the people, the way they live and go about their daily lives, what we do should resonate very well with them.</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operator</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And the next question will come from Edward Kelly of Credit Suisse.</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Judah Frommer</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Hi, guys.&#160;&#160;This is actually Judah on for Ed.&#160;&#160;On the synergies, following up there, the $40 million, do you have any preliminary expectations on how much is it investment in price versus labor, or kind of ballpark there?</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We think we&#8217;ll be able to hit the ground running very quickly.&#160;&#160;Bob knows investments he wants to make.&#160;&#160;As you know, they&#8217;ve launched the Wisconsin Proud program recently where they took some pricing investments.&#160;&#160;He&#8217;s been somewhat hamstrung with the leverage they&#8217;ve had on their balance sheet to do everything he would have wanted to do.&#160;&#160;So, I think Bob has a pretty good feel of exactly what he wants to do.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We&#8217;ll also identify some stores, and go in and refresh some of their footprint in Madison and Milwaukee so the customer understands what we&#8217;re going to stand for in the future.&#160;&#160;So, I&#8217;m real excited about the opportunity.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Judah Frommer</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;And for Mariano&#8217;s, do you have expectations around plans for additional expansion within Chicago, and maybe going outside of the Chicago area, which I know Bob was kind of hesitant to do in the near-term?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yeah, again, I think Bob has a well formulated plan of what he wants to do.&#160;&#160;He&#8217;s also been living with the reality of what he could do with the free cash flow that we generate on an annual basis.&#160;&#160;And again, I would look at that the same way as I would look at Wisconsin and how we&#8217;ll make investments there.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We&#8217;ll develop a solid plan for both the Chicago market and the Wisconsin market.&#160;&#160;And we feel we have ample dollars built into our model to be able to support growth in both store count and revenue in both markets.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Judah Frommer</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;Great.&#160;&#160;Thank you.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">You bet.</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operator</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And next, we have a question from Karen Short of Deutsche Bank.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Karen Short</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Hi.&#160;&#160;I have a couple of questions.&#160;&#160;Just looking at Roundy&#8217;s, I mean I see your $40 million number in the press release, but I&#8217;m curious just about overhead elimination in terms of the Roundy&#8217;s banner in general.&#160;&#160;I mean it would seem to me that there&#8217;s considerable overhead that may go away so that your estimates are somewhat conservative on the accretion.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yeah.&#160;&#160;You always think we&#8217;re conservative though, Karen.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Karen Short</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yeah, Krogy&#8217;s conservative.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Is that it?&#160;&#160;Is that it?&#160;&#160;Yeah.&#160;&#160;I&#8217;m started to say Kroger and Roundy&#8217;s at the same didn&#8217;t I?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I wouldn&#8217;t go down the path of overhead elimination because as we step back and look at this, we want to make sure we have the right focus on the stores in Wisconsin as well, and there could be some shifting of folks, of how we are on the ground on a daily basis.&#160;&#160;Our structure of how we manage our stores is a little bit different than them.&#160;&#160;We would have perhaps more folks in some of our district teams making sure that the stores are running the way we want them to run.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And some of the overhead could be a reallocation that we believe will drive better store conditions on a regular basis, which will ultimately lead to better sales results, which will ultimately lead to better EBITDA generation.&#160;&#160;So, some of that&#8217;s up in the air right now, and it&#8217;s way too early to speculate on overhead.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Karen Short</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;And then, I guess just looking at the legacy conventional banners, I mean obviously we all see what the comps are, and Roundy&#8217;s had more recently been giving us comps at both banners.&#160;&#160;And it&#8217;s clear that the conventional are struggling.&#160;&#160;It partly seems to be a competitive issue.&#160;&#160;So, I guess can you maybe help us get comfortable with why&#8212;what you think you can do?&#160;&#160;And I appreciate it might have been a balance sheet issue from Bob&#8217;s perspective in terms of being restricted on his abilities.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Karen, in many respects, when I talk to their team and I&#8217;m in Wisconsin, I kind of feel like Kroger did in the early part of the century as we were facing a lot of Wal-Marts coming into our markets, and our results were struggling.&#160;&#160;Certainly sales were struggling.&#160;&#160;And until we stepped back and created the Customer First strategy with the four prongs that&#8217;s when things really turned around.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Now, they&#8217;ve made some price moves.&#160;&#160;There will probably be more.&#160;&#160;As I said, they&#8217;re not as far off the market as we were when we started the journey.&#160;&#160;But, this feels very much like&#8212;if you think about this, it&#8217;s one Kroger division that&#8217;s just going to begin the Customer First journey about a third of the way into it.&#160;&#160;And that&#8217;s what gives us the comfort is they have started to make strides.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We need to spend some money in the stores, inside the stores, some capital money.&#160;&#160;That&#8217;s built in.&#160;&#160;Bob&#8217;s helping us understand where we should spend that first to get the biggest bang.&#160;&#160;They do have a loyalty card.&#160;&#160;So, the richness of the data, we think, is going to be very robust.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;ll be able to immediately run that through the algorithms that 84.51 brings to us, and hopefully get some of the same</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Priya Ohri-Jupta</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
&#160;</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">When we look at the debt, I would say that the term loan and things like that will be refinanced quickly.&#160;&#160;I believe the bonds have call options with a slight premium that actually start this December.&#160;&#160;They are secured with some liens against things.&#160;&#160;So, we want to be careful not to get debt like that into the Kroger capital structure.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, I would expect to see us to figure out how to refinance their debt in the very near-term.&#160;&#160;I won&#8217;t rush to the market&#8212;ultimately, I&#8217;ll issue long-term debt, but I won&#8217;t rush to the market to do it if the market is a little choppy &#8216;cause I do have plenty of dry powder in my revolver at a very great rate, and I&#8217;ll refinance the debt over the time when the market conditions are right for it.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Priya Ohri-Jupta</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">That&#8217;s very helpful.&#160;&#160;Thank you.</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yep.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operator</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And the next question comes from Rupesh Parikh of Oppenheimer.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Rupesh Parikh</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Thanks for taking my question.&#160;&#160;So, Mike, I wanted to delve further into maybe on the [indiscernible] diving side.&#160;&#160;If you can maybe help us understand how penetrated Roundy&#8217;s is in natural, organic and private label versus Kroger.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">They have a good offering of both.&#160;&#160;They use a third party for most of their private label.&#160;&#160;We think the private label area is something that can be beneficial.&#160;&#160;I would be surprised if early on in this process a banner like Private Selection and Simple Truth wouldn&#8217;t be some labels that we would look at getting into both banners relatively quick.&#160;&#160;I would say most of those conversations and thought processes, now that the merger has started, we can start having some high level conversations about those kinds of things.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Certainly when you look at the Mariano&#8217;s stores, there&#8217;s a big emphasis on fresh and natural and organic kinds of product.&#160;&#160;And we know how well that product resonates with customers.&#160;&#160;Love the fact that they have the richness of the data of their loyalty card to be able to understand what their customers are buying inside the store.&#160;&#160;But even more importantly, what they aren&#8217;t buying, and how to make sure that what they aren&#8217;t buying, that we know they&#8217;re probably buying somewhere, that we can figure out a way to make sure they know we&#8217;re going to have that product and it&#8217;s going to be high quality at a good price.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, we love the fact that they have that card that&#8217;s going to help us understand that.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Rupesh Parikh</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;Great, and one more question I had.&#160;&#160;As you look at Kroger store base, what portion of that base would you consider as urban stores?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Oh, gosh.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Scott Mushkin</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, my first one, Mike, is obviously the Mariano&#8217;s asset is a great asset, and I think your assessment is dead on.&#160;&#160;I guess with the bonds, I think we&#8217;re trading before the acquisition about $0.56 on the dollar.&#160;&#160;I guess why now, and why pay such a premium if the business was this tough and it looked like the bond market was saying maybe they weren&#8217;t working out.&#160;&#160;They&#8217;d have to file.&#160;&#160;So, I just wanted your insight on why now?&#160;&#160;Why the premium?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Well, I understand the headline premium looks very, very high.&#160;&#160;Keep in mind when you&#8217;re trading at a number that starts with a two it doesn&#8217;t take much of an increase in the offer to make the premium sound very high on an equity basis.&#160;&#160;It&#8217;s a significantly different looking premium when you look on an enterprise value basis of what they closed at yesterday and what they&#8217;re trading at today.&#160;&#160;I think if you look at an EBITDA multiple, it&#8217;s reasonable compared to other deals that have transacted out there with or without synergies.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I think the &#8220;Why now&#8221; is sometimes these things just come together at a particular point in time.&#160;&#160;And they still have very strong sales and market leadership in Wisconsin.&#160;&#160;We know they&#8217;ve had some supercenters come in via both Wal-Mart and [indiscernible] out of Grand Rapids.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;ve proven the ability to compete with those folks, and it&#8217;s just one of those things, that the deal happened when it happened.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And I know where the bonds were trading.&#160;&#160;That&#8217;s only a couple hundred million dollars of the capital structure.&#160;&#160;Most of the debt that&#8217;s out there is the term loan.&#160;&#160;And it just felt like the right time.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And as you and I have talked over time, the people box was checked and the real estate location box</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">was checked, and it just came together now.&#160;&#160;And we&#8217;re thrilled that it did, and Bob&#8217;s thrilled that it did.&#160;&#160;And he&#8217;s energized and can&#8217;t wait to be able to execute some of the strategies that he&#8217;s done slowly, and we&#8217;ll enable him to do it a little bit faster.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Scott Mushkin</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Oh, he&#8217;s getting a diamond in the rough with the Mariano&#8217;s.&#160;&#160;So, that&#8217;s good stuff.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So my second question is you&#8217;re going to be a little bit over two times, I guess, once you close on the debt metrics.&#160;&#160;And how do we think about other M&amp;A?&#160;&#160;I mean the business, the industry I should say, is clearly having some rough times; certainly certain operators.&#160;&#160;We may see more assets come free maybe in the southeast, maybe in other places.&#160;&#160;How do we think about other M&amp;A now that we&#8217;ve done this transaction?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yeah.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;ll still be comfortably inside our two to 2.2 times ratio.&#160;&#160;Obviously, we&#8217;ve communicated with the rating agencies.&#160;&#160;They understand what we&#8217;re doing.&#160;&#160;They&#8217;ve asked a lot of the same questions you all have asked relative to this is a little bit different; why now.&#160;&#160;But, a lot of this is things we&#8217;ve done.&#160;&#160;Even the Harris Teeter deal; we&#8217;ve obviously invested a lot of money and pricing there.&#160;&#160;So, it&#8217;s not unusual for us to merge with a chain that needs some price investment.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">This one needs a little bit more investment in the infrastructure than some of the other deals we&#8217;ve done.&#160;&#160;But again, we love the real estate locations, and just really excited for this to be part of the Kroger team.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Scott Mushkin</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, does it preclude further&#8212;</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I would say no.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;re comfortably inside the two to 2.2 times.&#160;&#160;Obviously with Harris Teeter, we went above 2.2 times, had the conversations with the rating agencies that we would manage our way back down to that ratio.&#160;&#160;Did it in 12 months instead the 18 to 24 we promised them.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;re very transparent with the rating agencies, with the level of cash flow we have.&#160;&#160;We have the ability to move levers around, and make sure that if an opportunity comes up that we have the dry powder to take advantage of it.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Scott Mushkin</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">That&#8217;s perfect.&#160;&#160;And then my third and final question, and I appreciate you taking them all, is Roundy&#8217;s is a little bit different than Harris Teeter.&#160;&#160;You got the union in there.&#160;&#160;They have a Central State Pension.&#160;&#160;Any thoughts on that Central State Pension?&#160;&#160;I know Roundy&#8217;s has been trying to do some work on that, and just kind of that attractiveness of that Wisconsin market given they&#8217;re losing population.&#160;&#160;So, just kind of general thoughts.&#160;&#160;I mean I think Chicago I get.&#160;&#160;I think the Wisconsin one with the pension issue and some other things, can you maybe talk to that?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Well, clearly we understand the pension issues as well as anybody and factored the obligations they have either on their balance sheet, or off their balance sheet into our valuation of the entity.&#160;&#160;It was certainly built into our view of value.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And I wouldn&#8217;t shy away from the Wisconsin market.&#160;&#160;There are still plenty of folks there, and still plenty of sales available.&#160;&#160;And in my mind, I agree with your comment.&#160;&#160;I don&#8217;t even know if I would call Mariano&#8217;s a diamond in the rough because we like a lot of what Bob&#8217;s done.&#160;&#160;I think our ability to restore</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify">

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We want the folks of Wisconsin to understand that they&#8217;re going to have a different experience going forward, and hopefully a much better shopping experience.&#160;&#160;I would tell you it&#8217;s not unlike 10 or 12 years with Kroger when we added the shopping experience [indiscernible].&#160;&#160;I would tell you our customers today tell you the shopping experience at Kroger is dramatically different than it was 10 or 12 years ago.&#160;&#160;And we hope to be able to export that to Wisconsin and get those customers as excited as the rest of the markets that we&#8217;re in today [indiscernible] those customers are.</font></div>

</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operator</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And the next comes from Chuck Cerankosky of Northcoast Research.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Chuck Cerankosky</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Good morning, everyone, and congratulations to Kroger on this pending transaction.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Thanks.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Chuck Cerankosky</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Hey, Mike, could you give us an idea of what the cadence, or pace might be of achieving that $40 million in synergy?&#160;&#160;You said it&#8217;s over the long-term, but is that two to three years, or three to five, and how much comes early rather than late?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">But also, it sounds like much of it is going to be supply chain opportunities.&#160;&#160;Are those going to be, in fact, addressed first, and will they immediately be rolled into price and service before we see it helping the bottom line of the overall company?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yeah.&#160;&#160;I won&#8217;t go too far on your question, Chuck.&#160;&#160;But obviously having Harris Teeter experience very recent, it&#8217;s given us great insight to where we would expect to find some bigger dollars early on.&#160;&#160;And we&#8217;re comfortable to be able to get a good number of dollars fairly quickly without any disruption to the people in the organization based on our learnings with Harris Teeter.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;ve gotten a great amount of synergies out of that transaction, and there have been no headcount reductions at Harris Teeter.&#160;&#160;And I think we&#8217;ll have the same experience here.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We know exactly where they are.&#160;&#160;Some of its services.&#160;&#160;Some of it&#8217;s being able to buy at different price levels.&#160;&#160;There&#8217;s a litany of things, and places that we&#8217;ll wind up getting it.&#160;&#160;You just think about&#8212;just start with the cost of being a public company that goes away.&#160;&#160;That saves a chunk of money right off the top.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, there are things like that that will happen pretty quickly that will enable us to hit the ground running.</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I think as we go down the path of getting this merger closed and we develop the joint strategy with Bob and his team, the way I would look at it is everything we have in our arsenal will be on the table.&#160;&#160;And we&#8217;ll deploy those items first that make the most sense, are going to resonate the most.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">As we&#8217;ve rolled out fuel centers, it obviously has been good for Kroger.&#160;&#160;We like the business.&#160;&#160;Most of these stores are leased.&#160;&#160;I wish they were owned, but most of them area leased.&#160;&#160;So, that usually means from a fuel center standpoint you&#8217;re negotiating with landlords.&#160;&#160;That in some cases is easier than others.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, we&#8217;ll develop a strategy for everything that&#8217;s made Kroger what Kroger is today from the four legs of the Customer First strategy, from the use of 84.51, analyzing their customer data, and really all the different merchandising techniques we&#8217;ve done.&#160;&#160;And we&#8217;ll deploy those as it makes sense, and we can do it.&#160;&#160;You don&#8217;t want to overwhelm the people either, but you want to get going quickly.&#160;&#160;So, it&#8217;s a fine balance there.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Joe Edelscein</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yeah.&#160;&#160;Well, they have 101 pharmacies, and we self-distribute pharmaceuticals, and that was a nice savings in the Harris Teeter transaction.&#160;&#160;I would expect that to be one of the earlier buckets of synergy savings.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Relative to clinics, we don&#8217;t have clinics in every market.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;re in the process right now of trying to dense up the markets where we are and get the right number.&#160;&#160;Rather than using a shotgun approach of putting a few everywhere, we&#8217;re trying to do it more of a rifle shoot, to get this city done, then get this city done.&#160;&#160;You get that core.&#160;&#160;It becomes a business that you stand for not unlike fuel.&#160;&#160;We don&#8217;t have fuel at every location, but customers figure out where the fuel is closest to their house so they can buy it, and I would look at clinics the same way.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">There are plenty of other markets where we don&#8217;t have clinics yet either that at some point in time, I would think that would be on the table to discuss as well.</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Hi, Mark.</font></div>
