</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mark Wiltamuth</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">First, I just wanted to confirm that the $40 million of synergies is operational and kind of exclusive of savings you&#8217;ll get on interest expense from refinancing.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yeah.&#160;&#160;It&#8217;s a little bit of everything.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mark Wiltamuth</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;And then, maybe just get your temperature&#8212;</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Keep in mind, Mark, if you just step back and did the math on interest expense, it winds up being pretty big.&#160;&#160;One of the ways I want to think about it is when I look at the capital I&#8217;m going to invest in this market, I would be charging myself for the interest on that new investment.&#160;&#160;So, if I spent $100 million of capital, I wouldn&#8217;t do that as interest free in the market.&#160;&#160;I would &#8220;charge,&#8221; if you will, the division for that interest expense.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, while it may go down a lot quickly, it&#8217;ll creep back up as I deploy capital in the market and give them an interest change if that makes sense.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mark Wiltamuth</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Right.&#160;&#160;And then, maybe you could help us think about the reinvestment back into the business.&#160;&#160;How much is this going to step on accretion?&#160;&#160;You&#8217;re saying slightly accretive here in near-term, but could we get up to like a Harris Teeter level of accretion like a few years out?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yeah.&#160;&#160;I&#8217;m not going to speculate out into the future.&#160;&#160;We have a great work plan designed for the first couple of years to get the business reinvigorated, get the sales momentum back into Wisconsin stores.&#160;&#160;And we do have bigger expectations out into the future, but I won&#8217;t go there at this point.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mark Wiltamuth</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;And just back to Mariano&#8217;s, do you think there&#8217;s an opportunity to take that entire business model and move it into other markets?&#160;&#160;I mean that 5% EBITDA margin that they target is relatively low, and there is a pretty low center of store pricing strategy there.&#160;&#160;Do you like the whole strategy they&#8217;ve got financially, or do you think you&#8217;ll just be picking and choosing the parts you like as you move forward?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yeah.&#160;&#160;I think what makes us a little unique in how we do these is we try to figure out the best sum of the parts.&#160;&#160;And my guess is as we deploy things, there&#8217;ll be facets that came from a Harris Teeter.&#160;&#160;There&#8217;ll be facets that came from a Mariano&#8217;s.&#160;&#160;There&#8217;ll be facets that came from a Kroger, or name the banner, Fresh Fare kind of store.&#160;&#160;And we&#8217;re continually evolving our offering, and we don&#8217;t stand static.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I mean if you think about when we first did Marketplace stores and converted the stores after the Fred Meyer merger in Phoenix, and if you look at the Marketplace stores of today, they still say &#8220;Marketplace&#8221; on it, but they&#8217;re dramatically different as we learned over time.&#160;&#160;And I would think about</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify">
<div><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">16</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mark Wiltamuth</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;And then just strategically, do you think you&#8217;re going to be making more of a push into natural, organic, urban now that you have more tools in your tool chest?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Rodney has often said this.&#160;&#160;It&#8217;s probably safe to assume if there&#8217;s some kind of a format out there that seems successful you should assume we&#8217;re trying it, or testing it somewhere.&#160;&#160;We just don&#8217;t talk about it.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mark Wiltamuth</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;Well, thank you very much.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">You bet.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operator</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">The next question is from Meredith Adler of Barclays.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Meredith Adler</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I was just about to remove my question because I guess I&#8217;ll just follow-up with Mark, just ask you; I had heard that Mariano&#8217;s provided a great customer experience, but wasn&#8217;t necessarily that profitable, but I don&#8217;t follow Roundy&#8217;s.&#160;&#160;Is there something that you are particularly focused on to make that format more profitable, or just sharing your scale and best practices?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I think it&#8217;s a little bit of all of that, Meredith.&#160;&#160;And they&#8217;re burdened with the same overhead costs that anybody&#8217;s burdened with.&#160;&#160;I mean when you think about 150 store chain being a public company, just taking that public company cost and burdening all the stores with it makes it tough, a tough environment to operate in.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Frankly, I think that&#8217;s one of the things Harris Teeter was going to start to run up against as Publix entered into Charlotte.&#160;&#160;How could they as a couple hundred, 50 store chain make the investments they needed to make in Charlotte to compete against Publix as they came into that market and didn&#8217;t just give share away?&#160;&#160;I think that&#8217;s one of the tipping points Harris Teeter had.&#160;&#160;And when you&#8217;re the public company like that, take away the focus of Wall Street wondering how you&#8217;re going to do; just the overhead and expense of being a public company become quite a burden on just 150 stores.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">My expense of a public company isn&#8217;t dramatically different.&#160;&#160;It&#8217;s a little bit higher, but I get to spread it over 2,600 stores.&#160;&#160;It&#8217;s like putting in a new computer system, our QVision system.&#160;&#160;I couldn&#8217;t have afforded QVision if I was 150 chain store, or 150 store chain.&#160;&#160;When I spread that over 2,600 stores, now almost 2,800 stores, those kinds of things become very, very affordable because the allocation to each store is so small and the benefit is so big that you can get a great return on those kinds of investments.&#160;&#160;And I would expect things like that to happen not only in Chicago, but Wisconsin as well.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Meredith Adler</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;Great.&#160;&#160;Thank you.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yep.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Todd Duvick</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Hi, Mike.&#160;&#160;Just a couple of balance sheet questions, follow-up from some previous questions.&#160;&#160;Given that the $800 million acquisition is going to elevate your leverage, but keep it within the range, should we expect all $800 million to be termed out in the debt capital markets, or just a portion?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I would say we had a bond&#8212;we, Kroger, had a bond that matured here recently that we paid off with commercial paper as well.&#160;&#160;And we&#8217;ll develop a strategy for how much of that and this we&#8217;ll term out.&#160;&#160;I like keeping a fair amount on my commercial paper out there.&#160;&#160;I like being in the market on a regular basis with commercial paper.&#160;&#160;It&#8217;s obviously my cheapest form of debt and, yeah, I realize some day interest rates are going to go up, but commercial paper will still probably for a very long time be my cheapest form of debt.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, we like to make sure that we are exposed all the way along the maturity curve, and we&#8217;ll be pretty thoughtful about where we place this debt, one, from an annual amount of maturities, as well as making sure that we&#8217;re exposed to different spots on the yield curve.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Todd Duvick</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;That&#8217;s helpful.&#160;&#160;And then in terms of timing, most likely this transaction is going to close by the end of the year if it goes as planned.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;re probably going to be looking for you in the market sometime after the first of the year.&#160;&#160;Is that a reasonable expectation?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yeah.&#160;&#160;I&#8217;ll be non-committal in exactly when we&#8217;ll access the market.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Todd Duvick</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Fair enough.&#160;&#160;Thank you.</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operator</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">The next question comes from Filippe Goossens of MUFG.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Filippe Goossens</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yes.&#160;&#160;Good morning, Mike.&#160;&#160;Thanks for taking my question.&#160;&#160;I actually have a two-part question.&#160;&#160;And the first one actually has been answered already through your comments this morning.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Basically, what I was trying to ascertain was to what an extent the acquisition of Roundy&#8217;s was driven by strategic reasons, i.e. get into the urban market format, or strengthen your present Chicago market versus a turnaround story because historically, you have not really done turnaround stories.&#160;&#160;So, I think this one probably is a little bit of a mix of both objectives.&#160;&#160;Is that a correct assessment for that question, Mike?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">It&#8217;s a little bit of a mix.&#160;&#160;I would agree with that.&#160;&#160;But, again, I go back to the real estate in Wisconsin.</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify">

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">18</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And let&#8217;s say I decided I wanted to enter Wisconsin as a new market, or Milwaukee, just Milwaukee as a new market as we&#8217;ve talked about going into new markets.&#160;&#160;The amount of time it would take for me to get 88 locations, I think that&#8217;s what they have, in Milwaukee.&#160;&#160;The Pick &#8216;n Saves, there&#8217;s 88 of them.&#160;&#160;The time it would take me to get 88 stores and the ability to get them located where they&#8217;ve been located for a very long time would take quite a while.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">When you go into a new market, you usually lose a little bit of money early on because you&#8217;re entering the market.&#160;&#160;You have a lot of overhead.&#160;&#160;You have one store.&#160;&#160;So, if I put an ad in the street, it&#8217;s the same price to put an ad in the street for one store or 88 stores.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, we look at this as we&#8217;re going into these markets as a new market, but we&#8217;re going in with a $4 billion book of business, great market share, and some EBITDA already.&#160;&#160;And we feel we can grow from here.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Filippe Goossens</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Great.&#160;&#160;And then my second question, Mike, a little bit more holistic I would say in nature, and kind of piggybacking on an earlier question from somebody.&#160;&#160;With regard to future M&amp;A interest, if I look at your portfolio, Mike, am I correct to recall that right now, you only have kind of one format that kind of comes close to a limited assortment store format, i.e. Food 4 Less?&#160;&#160;And the reason I&#8217;m asking is yesterday, I picked up in the European press that [indiscernible] has set up a headquarters in Arlington, Virginia, planning to open their first stores in 2018 [indiscernible] and then growing very quickly thereafter.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Now, if we&#8217;ve seen, or if we observed what they have done together with all the end UK markets where they have now an 8% market share and have really caught some headaches, I guess, for the incumbent traditional supermarket, is that a format that could be of interest for you.&#160;&#160;You&#8217;ve been very successful on the natural food side with the Simple Truth label.&#160;&#160;Do you also envision that at some point in time you may do something on the more limited assortment side of the market?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Well, as I said in response to, I think, Mark&#8217;s question, it&#8217;s probably safe to assume if there&#8217;s something out there we&#8217;ve been trying it.&#160;&#160;We actually have 30-some what we call ruler stores that are limited assortment that we continue to try to understand what&#8217;s the right offering, and the right customer acceptance of those models.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;ve obviously competed against Save A Lot for a very long time and compete against a significant number of ALDIs already.&#160;&#160;We&#8217;ve been very aware of the fact that Leedle [ph] has brought the property in the Virginia area and [indiscernible] market.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We always build our business model assuming things aren&#8217;t going to get easier, that they&#8217;re probably going to continue to stay tough over time, and we face a lot of that kind of competition today.&#160;&#160;And I don&#8217;t want to be dismissive of it because both ALDI and Leedle are great operators.&#160;&#160;But, we understand what makes them tick, and we spend a lot of time not just in stores in the US, but worldwide, and we&#8217;re impressed with what they do, but again, we&#8217;ve continued to be successful in markets where we have a lot of ALDIs and Save A Lots already.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Filippe Goossens</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Great.&#160;&#160;Thank you so much for that insight, Mike.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yep.</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Yeah.&#160;&#160;Hi.&#160;&#160;Good morning.&#160;&#160;Thanks for taking my question.&#160;&#160;My first question is just high level in terms of whether there&#8217;s been a shift in your acquisition strategy.&#160;&#160;I think at the recent investor conference, I believe you mentioned that you weren&#8217;t really looking to enter markets since Harris Teeter offered an opportunity to expand into the DC market.&#160;&#160;So, I think that recent commentary represented maybe a shift in your acquisition strategy compared to what was said back in 2012, during that investor conference.</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, do you have any feedback, Mike, on how Roundy&#8217;s might seem, at least on the surface, a little inconsistent, or might have a different profile compared to I think it was Rodney&#8217;s recent commentary on acquisition strategy.&#160;&#160;So, I&#8217;m just wondering; are you being completely opportunistic at this point, or is there a clearly defined strategy?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Let me try to tie all the different comments together, and I&#8217;m going to try to make sure everybody understands exactly what we&#8217;ve been trying to say because sometimes we think we&#8217;ve been crystal clear, but we know it can be subject to interpretation.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Back in 2012, we did say we were interested in entering some new markets organically.&#160;&#160;Then the Harris Teeter opportunity came; certainly put going into a new market organically on the back burner.&#160;&#160;They had DC as a new market, and we were learning a lot of how they went into that market as a new market organically before we were to go to one.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We continue to evaluate new markets organically.&#160;&#160;What we have said since the Harris Teeter merger is that&#8217;s put it on a little bit of a back burner with that opportunity.&#160;&#160;And as I said earlier in the call, when you have the opportunity to enter essentially two new markets, now really three or four new markets when you look at the Wisconsin market and you start out with a book of business of nearly $4 billion, the EBITDA that they generate already; while it&#8217;s new markets, it&#8217;s new markets with a little bit of momentum and a base of business behind it where you don&#8217;t start at zero and you&#8217;re going to throw off losses for a while when you enter a new market.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, I honestly don&#8217;t feel as though we&#8217;ve been inconsistent.&#160;&#160;I think the conversation has been about whether there&#8217;s an M&amp;A opportunity, or whether we enter a new market organically.&#160;&#160;I would say if anything, entering a new market organically each time we do a merger like this probably slows that thought process down a little because we want to make sure the merger is successful.&#160;&#160;But, we&#8217;re not afraid to enter a new market via a merger like this.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">AJ Jain</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;That was very helpful and actually, it did tie everything together.&#160;&#160;I had one follow-up.&#160;&#160;So, I understand that you&#8217;re expecting this to be immediately accretive and so notwithstanding&#8212;</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">AJ Jain</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operator</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">And the next question comes from Stacie Rabinowitz of Consumer Edge Research.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Stacie Rabinowitz</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">I was just curious.&#160;&#160;With more stores in the Chicago market and Chicago being such a consolidated geography, does that change how you&#8217;re thinking about what you might be testing in e-commerce and delivery versus pick-up?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We have probably a test of everything going on in e-commerce when you think about [indiscernible] cost and online ordering delivered to home via that way, when you think about express lane at Harris Teeter, Click List at Kroger, or home delivery in the Denver market.&#160;&#160;So, it&#8217;s safe to assume that we have things going on of all facets of this.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">As Rodney said at the investor conference a couple of weeks ago, this isn&#8217;t an &#8220;or.&#8221;&#160;&#160;It&#8217;s not shop in the store, or get home delivery.&#160;&#160;We view it as &#8220;and&#8221; and we do believe we have to solve for how the customer wants to interact us on each shopping trip.&#160;&#160;So, if they want to come to the store today, or if they want to drive by and have us put it in their cars, or if they want it delivered to their home, we believe we need to figure out a way to be able to address all of those needs for the customers.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Stacie Rabinowitz</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;Do you think that need for in-home delivery is greater in Chicago than some of the other areas you guys are currently in?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We&#8217;re not in Chicago.&#160;&#160;So, I don&#8217;t want to pretend I know the Chicago market intimately.&#160;&#160;Obviously, we&#8217;ve spent a lot of time there recently.&#160;&#160;I would say that when you step back from it, the higher use areas are denser urban markets like a New York, like a Philadelphia, like a Chicago.&#160;&#160;So, I would say that&#8217;s something that we&#8217;ll have Bob help us understand what his customers and now our customers in Chicago wants and needs are, and try to figure out a way to offer that to them.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Stacie Rabinowitz</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Thank you.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><font size="3" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">21</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
&#160;</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">All right.&#160;&#160;We have time for one more call.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operator</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Okay.&#160;&#160;That final question will come from Joseph Feldman of Delsey Advisory Group.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Joseph Feldman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Hey, guys.&#160;&#160;Thanks for taking the question.&#160;&#160;Most of mine were answered, but I did want to follow-up no something about the required investment for the stores that are up there.&#160;&#160;It sounds like Mariano&#8217;s are in very good shape, but the Wisconsin stores, and can you talk about how soon you&#8217;ll get in there to really start ramping up the actual store experience, and have you given thought to the level of expense that might be related to that?</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Well, we&#8217;re formulating a pretty detailed plan of where we would want to go and how, now, that this has been announced, we&#8217;ll start meeting with Bob and his team to formalize a joint plan.&#160;&#160;We have a particular view perhaps of where we may want to go first.&#160;&#160;We want to bounce that up against the people who have been running the stores and who know them better to make sure we haven&#8217;t missed the mark.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">We certainly have the ability to quickly, I believe quickly take their customer data, run it through the logarithms that 84.51 has and see what that tells us about where their pockets of the most loyal customers are that we would want to give a better shopping experience to.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">So, as all these different thoughts converge, one of the reasons that we expect this to be only slightly accretive early on, and we expect to reinvest a lot of these dollars is we would expect a fair amount of pace to this early on.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Joseph Feldman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Got it.&#160;&#160;That&#8217;s helpful, and the rest of my questions were answered.&#160;&#160;So, thanks, guys and good luck with it.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">CONCLUSION</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Mike Schlotman</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">Great.&#160;&#160;Thanks very much, and as Cindy said in her opening comments, thanks for joining us on short notice.&#160;&#160;And as always, thanks for the support you all give us every day.&#160;&#160;And I would like to close, once again, thanking all the veterans out there for their service to the country.&#160;&#160;Thanks very much and have a great day.</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; DISPLAY: inline">Operator</font></div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; DISPLAY: inline">The conference has now concluded.&#160;&#160;Thank you for attending today&#8217;s presentation.&#160;&#160;You may now disconnect.</font></div>

<div>&#160;</div>

Additional Information and Where to Find It</font></div>
</div>

<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; DISPLAY: inline">The tender offer referenced herein has not yet commenced. This communication is for informational purposes only and is neither an offer to purchase nor a solicitation of an offer to sell shares of Roundy&#8217;s, Inc. (&#8220;Roundy&#8217;s&#8221;), nor is it a substitute for the tender offer materials that The Kroger Co. (&#8220;Parent&#8221;) and KS Merger Sub Inc. (&#8220;Acquisition Sub&#8221;), a wholly-owned subsidiary of Parent, will file with the Securities and Exchange Commission (&#8220;SEC&#8221;) upon commencement of the tender offer. At the time the tender offer is commenced, Parent and Acquisition Sub will file with the SEC tender offer materials on Schedule TO, and Roundy&#8217;s will file with the SEC a Solicitation/Recommendation Statement on Schedule 14D-9, with respect to the tender offer. The tender offer materials (including an Offer to Purchase, a related Letter of Transmittal and certain other tender offer documents) and the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement will contain important information. Holders of shares of Roundy&#8217;s are urged to read these documents carefully when they become available, because they will contain important information that holders of Roundy&#8217;s securities should consider before making any decision regarding tendering their securities. The Offer to Purchase, the related Letter of Transmittal and certain other tender offer documents, as well as the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement, will be made available to all holders of shares of Roundy&#8217;s at no expense to them. The tender offer materials and the Solicitation/Recommendation Statement will be made available for free at the SEC&#8217;s web site at <font style="TEXT-DECORATION: underline; DISPLAY: inline">www.sec.gov</font>. Additional copies of the tender offer materials may be obtained at no charge by sending a written request to Parent at The Kroger Co., 1014 Vine Street, Cincinnati, OH 45202-1100, Attention: General Counsel.</font></div>

These statements are based on management's assumptions and beliefs in light of the information currently available to it. These statements are indicated by words such as "expect," "intend," "guidance,&#8221; &#8220;will" and similar words.&#160; Various uncertainties and other factors could cause actual results to differ materially from those contained in the forward-looking statements. These include the specific risk factors identified in "Risk Factors" and "Outlook" in Kroger&#8217;s annual report on Form 10-K for our last fiscal year and any subsequent filings, as well as the following:</font></div>
